Antennule (
Figure 1I
). Not exceeding the length of rostrum, about 1.7 times longer than wide; three rows of setulae on the antennular body. Antennular sensory seta slender, about 1.3 times smaller than antennular body, inserted in two-thirds of the antennule length from its base. Nine aesthetascs of different length, all projecting beyond the tip of rostrum. None of the aesthetascs exceeds the length of the antennules.
